The following is a rough first try at a README file for the
HepRep Visualization Driver.
Please forgive me if I much of the following is obvious.
I have tried to err on the side of completeness.

Instructions to build required freehep C++ library (Linux):

Need freehep version from Oct 31 20000 (later versions use HepRep2, not HepRep1).
Discussion of freehep checkout is at:
http://java.freehep.org/source.thtml

Check out freehep as follows:
setenv CVSROOT :pserver:anoncvs@cvs.freehep.org:/nfs/slac/g/jas/fhroot
cvs login
CVS Password: jascvs
cvs co -D 20001031 freehep

Make the freehep C++ library as follows:
setenv JDK_HOME /afs/slac.stanford.edu/package/java/i386_linux2/jdk1.3.1
setenv FREEHEP ~/wiredwork/freehep
setenv OS Linux
cd $FREEHEP
tools/bootstrap-freehep
tools/ant clean
tools/ant
gmake clean
gmake


Instructions to build Geant4 (Linux):

setenv CVSROOT /afs/cern.ch/sw/geant4/cvs
setenv G4 ~/wiredwork
setenv SCRATCH $BFROOT/work/p/perl
setenv G4INSTALL $G4/geant4
setenv G4BIN $SCRATCH/bin
setenv G4LIB $SCRATCH/lib
setenv G4TMP $SCRATCH/tmp
setenv G4SYSTEM Linux-g++
setenv G4LEVELGAMMADATA $G4INSTALL/data/PhotonEvaporation
setenv CLHEP_BASE_DIR $G4/CLHEP1.7
setenv G4VIS_BUILD_OPENGLX_DRIVER 1
setenv G4UI_BUILD_TERMINAL_SESSION 1
setenv G4UI_USE_TERMINAL 1
setenv OGLHOME /usr/X11
setenv G4VIS_BUILD_OPENGLXM_DRIVER 1
setenv G4UI_BUILD_XM_SESSION 1
setenv G4UI_USE_XM 1
setenv G4DEBUG 1
setenv G4VIS_USE_VRMLFILE
setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH /usr/local/lib:$CLHEP_BASE_DIR/lib
setenv G4VIS_USE_HEPREP 1
setenv FREEHEP ~/wiredwork/freehep
setenv JDK_HOME /afs/slac.stanford.edu/package/java/i386_linux2/jdk1.3.1
setenv G4_HEPREP_OSNAME linux
setenv G4_HEPREP_ARCH i386
setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH "$GLHEP_BASE_DIR/lib:
$FREEHEP/lib/Linux-g++:$JDK_HOME/jre/lib/i386/hotspot:$JDK_HOME/jre/lib/i386"
setenv CLASSPATH "$FREEHEP/lib/freehep-2d.jar:$FREEHEP/lib/freehep-heprep.jar:
$FREEHEP/lib/freehep-base.jar:$FREEHEP/lib/xerces.jar:$FREEHEP/lib/collections.jar"

cd $G4INSTALL/source
rm -r $G4TMP
gmake > & gmake.log &

cd $G4INSTALL/examples/novice/N03
gmake >& gmake.log &
or
cd $G4INSTALL/source/visualization/test
touch test19.cc
gmake


Instructions to run Geant4 to make heprep xml:

ln -s $G4BIN/Linux-g++/test19 .
test19
/vis/open HepRep
/vis/viewer/refresh
/vis/viewer/update

creates output file:
~/wiredwork/G4/geant4/source/visualization/test/HepRepTest.xml

Joseph Perl
24 August 2001